<subSubSection id="C3406515633EFFC4FF12F97AFD30F815" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE5369E633EFFC4FF12F97AFB10F927" blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FF12F97AFE8AF948" bold="true" box="[151,269,1676,1702]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Remarks:</emphasis>
The original collector’s label (
<figureCitation id="13612A1B633EFFC4FDF4F97AFD67F949" box="[625,736,1676,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,787,811]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,186,761]" captionTargetId="figure-24@16.[149,1437,181,763]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Labels of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection described by T. Salvadori. a) Ptilotis erythropleura NHMO-BI-86778 (collector’s label); b) Melanocharis chloroptera NHMO-BI-61863 (NHMO label); c) Zosterops novae guineae NHMO-BI-86649 (NHMO label); d) Dicaeum misoriense NHMO-BI-61856 (collector’s label)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626777/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Figure 6a</figureCitation>
) is still attached, showing that this is specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FA8CF97BFA90F948" box="[1289,1303,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">g</emphasis>
of the 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C633EFFC4FAE9F97BFA1BF949" box="[1388,1436,1677,1703]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">type</typeStatus>
series (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FF63F959FE11F927" author="Salvadori, T." box="[230,406,1711,1737]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori 1881</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FE5EF959FD84F927" box="[475,515,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">‘p.’</emphasis>
in the locality name is an abbreviation for 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FC61F959FBA9F927" box="[996,1070,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">‘piedi’</emphasis>
, i.e. feet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E633EFFC4FF42F927FC02F872" blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FF42F927FE31F905" author="Arbocco, G. &amp; Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C." box="[199,438,1745,1771]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="184 - 265" refId="ref13577" refString="Arbocco, G., Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C. (1979) Catalogo dei tipi di uccelli del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 82, 184 - 265." type="journal article" year="1979">
Arbocco 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FEABF924FEE1F905" box="[302,358,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
(1979)
</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD17633EFFC4FD85F927FD27F902" box="[512,672,1745,1772]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">three syntypes</specimenCount>
in Genoa (C.E. 11455–11457), and according to Enrico Borgo at the MSNG (pers. comm.) these are specimens 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FDF3F902FD03F8E0" box="[630,644,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">b</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FD14F902FD18F8E0" box="[657,671,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">h</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FD50F903FD5AF8E0" box="[725,733,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">i</emphasis>
, respectively, as listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FB87F902FB45F8E0" author="Salvadori, T." box="[1026,1218,1780,1806]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
. The latter of these, specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FE82F8E1FE88F8DE" box="[263,271,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">i</emphasis>
, is not one of the 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C633EFFC4FE50F8E1FDBCF8DF" box="[469,571,1815,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">syntypes</typeStatus>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FDC3F8E1FC85F8DF" author="Salvadori, T." box="[582,770,1815,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
stated that specimens 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FC79F8E1FBA1F8DF" box="[1020,1062,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">a–h</emphasis>
are the types, which is also in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FEBFF8CFFD84F8BA" author="Salvadori, T." box="[314,515,1849,1876]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="896 - 976" refId="ref16237" refString="Salvadori, T. (1876 a) Descrizione di cinquantotto nuove specie di uccelli, ed osservazioni intorno ad altre poco note, della Nuova Guinea e di altre Isole Papuane, raccolte dal D. r Odoardo Beccari e dai cacciatori del Sig. A. A. Bruijn. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 7, 896 - 976. [1875]" type="journal article" year="1876">Salvadori (1876a)</bibRefCitation>
basing his description on eight individuals only. Another 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C633EFFC4FB04F8CCFB5FF8BA" box="[1153,1240,1850,1876]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">syntype</typeStatus>
(MZUT Av4127) is in MRSN 
<quantity id="4CA29B7B633EFFC4FEA5F8ABFEC1F899" box="[288,326,1885,1911]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" unit="in" value="3.0">
<superScript id="7C2F9BD6633EFFC4FEA5F8ABFEAFF885" attach="left" box="[288,296,1885,1899]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">3</superScript>
in
</quantity>
Turin (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FE1EF8ABFD07F899" author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[411,640,1885,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FD84F8A8FDBCF899" box="[513,571,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
); this corresponds to specimen 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FC63F8A8FC75F899" box="[998,1010,1886,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">e</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FB9FF8ABFBA5F899" box="[1050,1058,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">f</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FBCCF8ABFA8DF899" author="Salvadori, T." box="[1097,1290,1885,1911]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, but its label does not indicate which of these it is (Luca Ghiraldi, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E633EFFC4FF12F850FD30F815" blockId="15.[151,1436,1676,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
3 The ornithological collection of the Zoological Museum of the Turin University (MZUT) has since the 1990s been hosted at the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (MRSN) in Turin, but the specimens in this collection have retained their MZUT inventory numbers (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F633EFFC4FE64F815FD2BF815" author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[481,684,2019,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C633EFFC4FDB9F812FDE8F815" box="[572,623,2019,2043]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
